{
  "texts": [
    "As indicated by prior research, few-shot GPT-3's performance is susceptible to instability and may decline to near chance levels due to the reliance on incontext examples.",
    "This instability becomes more pronounced when dealing with intricate problems such as TABMWP.",
    "In addressing this issue, Lu et al. (2023b) introduced PROMPTPG, which can autonomously learn to select effective in-context examples through policy gradient interactions with the GPT-3 API, eliminating the need for manually designed heuristics.",
    "LLMs, ranging from 2M to 137B in size.",
    "Their approach involved training these models to solve integer addition and polynomial evaluation by generating intermediate computation steps into a designated \"scratchpad.\""
  ]
}